definition: custom-designed cake (e.g. cake shaped like a guitar, camera or cartoon character)

sentences.english: They had pears in white wine, with a piece of fruitcake.
sentences.chinese: 他们吃着白葡萄酒腌泡过的梨子，配着水果蛋糕。

sentences.english: Moreover, bean curd cheese cake is also wonderful.
sentences.chinese: 此外，用豆腐做成的奶酪蛋糕也是特棒的。

sentences.english: The optimum recipe for ginger-cake processing was studied with orthogonal design.
sentences.chinese: 以正交实验研究了添加姜粉蛋糕的配方。

sentences.english: Nowhere in Uzhhorod have I seen things like this.
sentences.chinese: 我从没在乌日戈罗德的其它地方见过这样的蛋糕。

sentences.english: The dog soon ate up the nice cke.
sentences.chinese: 大狗很快就吃完了那块美味的蛋糕。

sentences.english: Hot and fresh out of the dishwasher.
sentences.chinese: 从洗碗机里新鲜出炉的热腾腾的蛋糕。

sentences.english: The peach pies and chocolate Mousse cakes are nearly finished.
sentences.chinese: 桃馅饼和巧克力慕斯蛋糕也接近卖完。

sentences.english: Here are some shortbread and some home-made cakes.
sentences.chinese: 这里还有点饼干和自己家做的蛋糕。

sentences.english: Cheesecake is a large family of sweet, cheese-based cakes.
sentences.chinese: 芝士蛋糕是一类用芝士作为基本材料的甜点。

sentences.english: The fruit cake has tantalized the world for centuries.
sentences.chinese: 几个世纪以来，水果蛋糕都是诱人的美味。

sentences.english: The kernel of the walnut is eaten by itself or used in cakes or cookies.
sentences.chinese: 胡桃仁可以直接食用或者用与蛋糕或饼干中。

sentences.english: Splendid cake, covered with cupids, silver, and true-lover's knots.
sentences.chinese: 用爱神，银纸，同心结等装饰着的上等蛋糕。

sentences.english: Put in the stack, and grab cakes served in the three new mini games.
sentences.chinese: 放在堆栈，抢蛋糕服务三个新的迷你游戏。

sentences.english: Our head teacher has shared the cake among all the students at the party.
sentences.chinese: 我们的班主任老师在晚会上把蛋糕分给每个学生。

sentences.english: Combine glaze ingredients; drizzle over cake.
sentences.chinese: 混合浇汁材料，淋在蛋糕上。

sentences.english: This grrrroovy groom puckers up for his new wife…
sentences.chinese: 这是婚礼上为新人们准备的蛋糕。

definition: cookie (loanword via Cantonese 曲奇 kuk1 kei4)
